data.name: tbxT206.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T205 To enable students to gain practical and technical networking knowledge that will allow them to configure and troubleshoot routers, switches and resolve common issues with RIPv1, RIPng, single-area and multi-area OSPF, virtual LANs, and inter-VLAN routing in both IPv4 and IPv6 networks. Learning Outcomes: - Describe basic switching concepts and the operation of Cisco switches - Describe the purpose, nature, and operations of a router, routing tables, and the route lookup process - Describe how VLANs create logically separate networks and how routing occurs between them - Describe dynamic routing protocols, distance vector routing protocols, and link-state routing protocols - Configure and troubleshoot static routing and default routing (RIP and RIPng) - Configure and troubleshoot an Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) network - Configure and troubleshoot access control lists (ACLs) for IPv4 and IPv6 networks - Configure and troubleshoot Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) for IPv4 and IPv6 networks - Configure and troubleshoot Network Address Translation (NAT) operations

data.name: tbxT205.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER To enable students to gain practical and technical networking knowledge that will assist them to build simple LANs, perform basic configurations for routers and switches, and implement IP addressing schemes. Learning Outcomes: - Describe the devices and services used to support communications in data networks and the internet - Describe the role of protocol layers in data networks - Describe the importance of addressing and naming schemes at various layers of data networks in IPv4 and IPv6 environments - Design, calculate, and apply subnet masks and addresses to fulfil given requirements in IPv4 and IPv6 networks - Explain fundamental Ethernet concepts such as media, services, and operations - Build a simple Ethernet network using routers and switches - Use Cisco command-line interface (CLI) commands to perform basic router and switch configurations - Utilise common network utilities to verify small network operations and analyse data traffic

data.name: tbxI213.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I111 To create a dynamic web application utilising a variety of open-source technologies Learning Outcomes: - Design and document a web application - Secure critical business data within the web application - Interface with a web based database management system - Implement user security and session management

data.name: tbxT301.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T201 To recommend uses for thin and thick client architectures and to design a thin client architecture. Students will be able to analyse and evaluate network designs, select an appropriate technology and design for a given situation, and justify their selection. Learning Outcomes: - Assess and recommend at least two different thin client technologies - Select an appropriate thin/thick architecture for a given situation and justify the selection - Evaluate the performance differences between different thin/thick architectures - Devise and create a proof of technology - Assess server and client virtualisation strategies

data.name: tbxI321.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREQUISITE PAPER: I221 To introduce tools and techniques used to assess feasibility and present a business case; to complete an analysis of a complex information system based on the recommendation from the feasibility phase. Learning Outcomes: - Undertake a feasibility study to recommend a solution to business problems - Present a business case to project stakeholders - Develop a model of the proposed complex system - Implement quality processes to ensure accuracy of analysis and design documentation

data.name: tbxT302.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T211 To provide the ability to design and construct a complex multi-user client/server network. Students will gain skills needed to configure and integrate complex systems. Learning Outcomes: - Create a multi-user implementation of a client/server network - Implement techniques to integrate multi-vendor operating systems - Implement a common authentication source for drivers systems which may include file, database, web and proxy servers - Devise and implement strategies which will ease the administrative burden through automation and log checking - Implement remote administration of central services - Assess the advantages and disadvantages of open source systems

data.name: tbxT311.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T206 To gain practical and technical networking knowledge that will assist in designing, building and analysing networks and their protocols using advanced technologies Learning Outcomes: - Configure and troubleshoot enhanced switching technologies such as VLANs, Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (RSTP), Per VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol (PVST+), and EtherChannel - Configure and troubleshoot first hop redundancy protocols (HSRP) in a switched network - Configure and troubleshoot wireless routers and wireless clients - Configure and troubleshoot routers in a complex routed IPv4 or IPv6 network using single-area OSPF, multi-area OSPF, and Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol (EIGRP) - Manage Cisco IOS Software licensing and configuration files - Describe different WAN technologies and their benefits - Describe the operations and benefits of virtual private networks (VPNs) and tunnelling - Configure and troubleshoot serial and broadband connections - Configure and troubleshoot Network Address Translation (NAT) operations - Configure and troubleshoot tunneling operations - Monitor and troubleshoot network operations using syslog, SNMP, and NetFlow - Describe network architectures: Borderless networks, Data centres and virtualization, Collaboration technology and solutions

data.name: tbxI303.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I201 To enable students to analyse and evaluate management practices as they relate to the ICT industry Learning Outcomes: - Discuss and analyse key issues associated with managing and structuring the ICT capability within an organisation - Recommend and design a quality management programme for an organisation - Apply best practice human resource management techniques - Commentate on relevant legislation and social responsibility issues as they relate to the ICT industry

data.name: tbxI302.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER PREREQUISITES: 285 credits including I301 and all compulsory level 5 & 6 papers To enable students to undertake an industry based project of a complex nature. Learning Outcomes: - Manage an ICT project for industry - Produce original work and project deliverables - Consider and apply professional work ethics - Meet project timelines and goals - Record and evaluate project work and progress - Present project outcomes to sponsors and academic supervisors

data.name: tbxI301.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER PREREQUISITES: 240 credits includes all level 5 & level 6 compulsory papers To apply communication theories and practice in a professional context. Students will also source an industry project and produce appropriate documentation. Learning Outcomes: - Analyse and evaluate applied communication principles - Demonstrate effective communication skills - Procure an industry based project - Create project scope documentation - Demonstrate ability to work in teams

data.name: tbxD202.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: D201 To create quality software applications utilising a modern development approach Learning Outcomes: - Undertake a team based iterative development project - Effectively manage an individual development task - Implement processes to ensure quality - Compare and select an appropriate development method for a given problem

data.name: tbxD201.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUSITE PAPER: D101 To introduce standard algorithms required for business application programming. Learning Outcomes: - Design and Construct small applications using a variety of algorithms - Devise test plans to ensure quality software - Create system maintenance documentation

data.name: tbxD303.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: D211 To develop a small, enterprise-level Java application that provides support for a mobile workforce Learning Outcomes: - Design and construct an application for a mobile device - Interface with business data held in a legacy relational database system

data.name: tbxD301.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: D201 To design and construct quality software ready for distribution Learning Outcomes: - Perform object-oriented design and programming with a high level of proficiency - Secure applications so that they are ready for distribution - Conduct effective and efficient inspections - Evaluate software user interfaces for accessibility and usability - Design and implement comprehensive test plans

data.name: tbxD311.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: D211 To enable a student to successfully design, create and administer a data warehouse using a server-based database management system. Learning Outcomes: - Discuss and argue a given data warehousing topic - Install a server-based database management system - Design and create a data warehouse schema - Transfer and transform data from more than one data source into a data warehouse - Analyse and process data for management reporting - View pre-processed information from the data warehouse from a separate application

data.name: tbxT211.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T111 To analyse and implement computer systems security, including operating systems, server applications & networks; and to enable students to explain the fundamentals of computer forensics. Learning Outcomes: - Demonstrate knowledge of operating systems security - Analyse the security and security weaknesses affecting operating systems - Demonstrate configuring operating system security - Analyse server application security considerations - Analyse and contrast server application technologies - Demonstrate successful implementation of a server application/s - Demonstrate theoretical and practically applied knowledge of securing server application technologies - Demonstrate knowledge of network security technology - Analyse and contrast network security technology - Demonstrate an ability to practically implement network security technologies - Demonstrate knowledge of computer forensic practices

data.name: tbxT201.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: T101 To implement key network services as used in modern LANs and to explain the network protocols that these services use. Learning Outcomes: - Implement and explain the operation of name resolution - Implement automatic network configuration - Implement and explain the operation of directory services - Implement and explain the operation of a web proxy - Implement automatic browser configuration when a web proxy is used - Implement and explain the operation of time synchronisation in the LAN - Implement a mail gateway and explain the operation of common email protocols

data.name: tbxI211.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I111 To introduce principles and application of electronic commerce technologies Learning Outcomes: - Define Electronic Commerce and describe its various categories - Describe the major types of Electronic Commerce transactions - Describe the limitations of Electronic Commerce - Develop an online commercial Web site for selling products - Implement user security and session management for the Web site

data.name: tbxI202.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I102 This paper will give an understanding of project management theory and practice as it relates to the ICT industry. Learning Outcomes: - Analyse and discuss the nine knowledge areas of project management - Demonstrate knowledge of project teams including co-located and virtual teams - Develop a project plan for an IT related project - Demonstrate the practical application of a project management tool

data.name: tbxI221.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I121 To create quality analysis and design documentation for a moderately complex system Learning Outcomes: - Compare and select an appropriate analysis methodology for a project - Create analysis documentation for a moderately complex system - Create design documentation for the system under investigation - Implement quality processes to ensure accuracy of analysis and design documentation

data.name: tbxI203.ToolTip
data.value: ELLECTIVE PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: I102 To apply principles and techniques relating to the application of digital multimedia technologies Learning Outcomes: - Describe the concepts of digital images, video and audio - Create and manipulate digital image, video and audio files according to a technical specification for distribution across the ICT infrastructure - Optimise digital multimedia for commonly used ICT mediums

data.name: tbxD211.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER PREREQUISITE PAPER: D111 To effectively design an information system for a complex business application Learning Outcomes: - Evaluate alternative design solutions - Design a complex information system - Create a prototype from a design - Formulate quality processes

data.name: tbxT111.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To gain an understanding of the fundamentals of computer hardware, operating systems and troubleshooting techniques. Learning Outcomes: - Demonstrate an understanding of computer hardware - Demonstrate practical troubleshooting skills with computer systems - Explain the performance determinants and metrics of computer systems - Demonstrate an understanding of the purpose and function of an operating system - Describe and demonstrate operating system management techniques. (e.g. process, memory, disk) -Demonstrate a practical knowledge of writing operating system scripts

data.name: tbxT101.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To provide an introduction to the fundamentals of computer networks as they currently exist in industry and to enable students to configure, test and troubleshoot local area networks. Learning Outcomes: - Classify computer networks. Examples may include but are not limited to LAN, MAN, WAN and PAN - Select the most appropriate network media for a given scenario. Network media will include fibre optic, copper and wireless - Describe the operation and performance of network protocols. Examples may include but are not limited to TCP/IP and Ethernet - Describe the operation and performance of network hardware. Examples may include but are not limited to hub, switches, routers and wireless access points - Describe the fundamentals of encryption and its application in computer networks - Describe the fundamentals of authentication in networks - Construct a small LAN using current operating systems and technology - Test and troubleshoot network problems

data.name: tbxI111.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To introduce the use of the World Wide Web (WWW) as an information medium Learning Outcomes: - Describe aspects of Internet history - Describe the common underlying protocols of the Internet - Describe current web development technologies - Interpret end user needs and design a web site to meet these needs - Construct a web site from a design using common web development techniques and applying good web design principles

data.name: tbxI102.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To enable students to understand the components of training and user support. Learning Outcomes: - Apply a user needs analysis - Create a training plan for a specified topic - Create a computer based training resource - Create paper based user documentation - Train a user - Evaluate training sessions - Demonstrate knowledge of user support

data.name: tbxI121.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To provide an introduction to the principles of systems analysis and systems requirements elicitation techniques Learning Outcomes: - Analyse situations requiring problem solving - Elicit and model user requirements using a variety of techniques - Construct accurate systems analysis documentation reflecting requirements

data.name: tbxI101.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To introduce students to business fundamentals and essential components of the ICT profession. Learning Outcomes: - Describe organisational entities and structures - Define legislative and ethical issues in relations to the ICT industry - Apply collaborative business tools - Describe information systems principles, roles and functional business areas - Use APA referencing in academic writing

data.name: tbxD101.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To provide an introduction to software engineering techniques and processes. Learning Outcomes: - Describe the software development lifecycle - Design small programs using an industry standard format - Write small programs in a current language - Systematically test and debug small programs

data.name: tbxD111.ToolTip
data.value: COMPULSORY PAPER To provide an introduction to data characteristics, data organisation and data management relating to a business environment. Learning Outcomes: - Describe common methods of data organisation - Describe common database models - Create a simple Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) - Construct a simple relational database using Structured Query Language (SQL) - Perform basic Data Manipulation Language (DML) operations on the database. - Use data integrity techniques
